race.comment: MISS EVEREST (1) used the rails draw to advantage to get home last time at Launceston over 278m (16.26), scoring by 4 lengths. Goes very well from this box, having won four times. Has the inside again and looks the one to beat. SHOW PRINCESS (2) turned in a solid run last start over 340m at this track finishing 5th and beaten only 1.4 lengths (19.70). Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from six starts. Can measure up this time. WHY SPARKY (7) ran below best last time finishing fourth (19.68) over 340m at this track from Box 8. Has a solid record from this box including three wins and a minor placing. Expected to feature in the finish. HIGHGATE SNIPER (6) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.
